    "Moreover, the dice scores on test set are calculated for all models after 5, 30 and 60 epochs.",
    "As shown in Table 2, the pretrained models converge faster than randomly initialized models and generally score higher, specially in the beginning epochs.",
    "The general trend of the results and observations for all other datasets is consistent with the above-reported ones.",
    "Comparison of segmentation Dice scores for different training methods (randomly initialized weights (R) and pretrained (P) with GANs on CEM500K using 50 K, 100 K, 200 K images) on the Au5nmV1 test dataset.",
